    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nConceal characters do not inherit the background of the text they conceal (not applicable when the conceal character highlight group has its own background color, of course)\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\n-- minimal.lua\nvim.treesitter.query.set(\n  'markdown',\n  'highlights',\n  [[((list_marker_star) @conceal\n    (#offset! @conceal 0 0 0 -1)\n    (#set! @conceal conceal \"â—¦\"))\n\n  (section) @test\n  ]]\n)\nvim.treesitter.highlighter.new(vim.treesitter.get_parser(0, 'markdown'))\nvim.wo.conceallevel = 2\nvim.wo.concealcursor = 'v'\nvim.bo.ft = 'markdown'\n\n-- Regular highlight background not respected\nvim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, '@test', { link = 'IncSearch' })\n\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, true, {\n  '* Test  ',\n  '  * Test',\n  '  * Test',\n  '  * Test',\n})\n\n-- Visual highlight background not respected\nvim.cmd.norm('Vj')\n\n-- Same with `hl-Folded`, etc.\n```\nthen `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe conceal characters should inherit the background of the characters they conceal\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNightly (442d338cb50e4cf08c58cb82b6d33b6d5df9fb1b)\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes, 9.1\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS 24.05, Linux 6.12.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.37.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nneovim-nightly-overlay (nix)",
